Zomato SQL Analysis Project
🔹 Overview
This project focuses on analyzing a food delivery dataset using SQL to understand customer behavior, spending patterns, and overall business performance.
Instead of just writing queries, the goal here was to solve practical business problems and interpret the results in a meaningful way.
________________________________________
🔹 What This Project Covers
The analysis answers key business questions related to:
•	Customer retention 
•	Revenue distribution 
•	Ordering frequency 
•	Cancellation and delivery performance 
•	Restaurant and customer contribution 
•	City-wise demand patterns 
________________________________________
🔹 Tools & Concepts Used
•	SQL (MySQL) 
•	Joins (INNER JOIN) 
•	Aggregations (SUM, AVG, COUNT) 
•	Window Functions (NTILE, LAG) 
•	Date Functions (DATEDIFF, STR_TO_DATE) 
________________________________________
🔹 Analysis & Insights
________________________________________
 Q1: What % of customers never place a second order?
Insight:
Only around 1% customers placed just one order, which indicates very high retention. However, this likely reflects a dataset biased toward active users rather than a real-world scenario.
________________________________________
 Q2: How much revenue is contributed by top 5% customers?
Insight:
Top 5% customers contribute only 8.85% of total revenue, showing that revenue is fairly distributed and not heavily dependent on a small group of users.
________________________________________Q3: What is the average time between consecutive orders?
Insight:
Customers take around 81.46 days between orders on average, indicating relatively low ordering frequency and potential scope to improve engagement.
________________________________________
Q4: What % of orders are cancelled?
Insight:
Around 9.83% of orders get cancelled, which is a noticeable portion and may point toward operational issues like delays or availability problems.
________________________________________
Q5: Which are the top 5 restaurants by revenue?
Insight:
A few restaurants consistently generate higher revenue than others, indicating that performance is uneven across partners and some outlets drive a larger share of sales.
________________________________________
Q6: What is the average order value?
Insight:
The average order value is ₹215, giving a sense of typical customer spending per order on the platform.
________________________________________
Q7: Which day has the highest number of orders?
Insight:
Orders peak on Wednesdays (14,572 orders), showing a clear mid-week spike in customer activity.
________________________________________
Q8: What % of orders are successfully delivered?
Insight:
Around 90.17% of orders are successfully delivered, indicating a fairly reliable delivery system with limited failures.
________________________________________
Q9: Who are the top 5 customers by total spending?
Insight:
Customers like Gautam Mane, Balveer Patla, Avni Ramaswamy, Tristan Hayer, and Pushti Kakar stand out in terms of spending. However, overall revenue is still not highly concentrated, as top users contribute a relatively small share (8.85%).
________________________________________
Q10: Which city generates the highest revenue?
Insight:
Mumbai generates the highest revenue (1,934,426), indicating stronger demand and higher order volumes compared to other cities.
